&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive II&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(Onsite - 5 days per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A successful Technical Account Executive II drives B2B client growth, technological adoption, and satisfaction within the Weedmaps dual-sided marketplace. The Account Executive will be measured on their success in driving revenue through technical solution-selling (including APIs, Point of Sale integrations, and logistics software), heading off and minimizing churn through product stickiness, and driving billing collection efforts. The Account Executive leads the complex sales growth and Ad Tech&amp;nbsp; revenue generation strategy for their assigned book, in partnership with their Account Manager(s).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The impact you&#39;ll make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pipeline &amp;amp; Quota Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage a technical book of business where recurring revenue (ARR/MRR) and Net Revenue Retention (NRR) goals are met and exceeded.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Discovery:&lt;/strong&gt; Conduct deep-dive qualification calls to understand the client&#39;s current tech stack, compliance hurdles, and inventory management pain points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution Pitching:&lt;/strong&gt; Introduce and pitch the full WM Business suite by demonstrating how API integrations, automated compliance guardrails, and logistics tech solve specific operational bottlenecks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration Consulting:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the bridge between Weedmaps&#39; technical capabilities and non-technical dispensary owners, specifically explaining the value of live PoS syncs to eliminate manual data entry and consumer cancellations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Expansion:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate with assigned Account Manager(s) to identify and close upsell opportunities, driving deeper product adoption to ensure the Weedmaps suite becomes the client&#39;s core infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketplace Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Educate B2B clients on dual-sided marketplace dynamics, using data to prove Return on Ad Spend (ROAS) and long-term Customer Lifetime Value (LTV) generated by Weedmaps&#39; consumer traffic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Advocacy:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as a technical product advocate by actively gathering quantitative and qualitative feedback from clients and sharing it directly with Product and Engineering teams to shape the roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk Mitigation:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify and predict churn risks early by monitoring technical utilization and adoption metrics, partnering with AM(s) to build mitigation plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Hygiene:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the steward of client data hygiene by maintaining rigorous CRM (Salesforce) records regarding integration status, tech stack updates, meeting notes, state compliance license validity, and billing payments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ve accomplished:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; BS / BA Degree or equivalent proven experience in technical sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum 3 years of experience in Ad Tech sales, account management, or technical platform sales in a client-facing role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Aptitude:&lt;/strong&gt; High-level understanding of APIs, data syncing, cloud-based architecture, and how software systems integrate (e.g., PoS to online marketplace).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical Approach:&lt;/strong&gt; Data-oriented sales approach with the ability to confidently present metrics like ROI, CAC, and LTV using business intelligence tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultativ

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Manager I&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(Onsite - 5 days per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account Manager drives client growth &amp;amp; satisfaction with Weedmaps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account Manager will be measured on their success in 1) driving revenue through identifying opportunities &amp;amp; optimizations 2) heading off &amp;amp; minimizing churn,and 3) drive billing collection efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The impact you&#39;ll make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage a book of business to meet and exceed revenue &amp;amp; retention goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide insights &amp;amp; recommendations to clients on how to grow their business with Weedmaps marketing solutions, based on the client &amp;amp; market data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with assigned Account Executive(s) on the best path to drive more value for your shared clients &amp;amp; enter opportunities in CRM for management visibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Increase the client’s proficiency &amp;amp; usage of the Weedmaps platform through training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular business reviews, sales presentations, product demonstrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the steward of the client data hygiene by updating &amp;amp; maintaining the CRM (or any other designated locations) on calls, meetings, contact info, current license, and up to date on billing payments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate billing updates proactively to drive collection efforts as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relay feedback from clients to improve our products and process to increase client success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ve accomplished:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS / BA Degree or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 1 year of experience in Ad Tech sales or account management; client/customer facing role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of hitting goals and revenue targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-oriented, analytical sales approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-centric and an eager relationship builder, with the ability to share feedback with customers to drive positive long-term relationship momentum (and not always just to appease in the moment)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidence in presenting to clients (onsite or on phone) to influence credibly and effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort with and ability to operate at an accelerated, iterative pace in a dynamic environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong planning and organizational skills with a clear attention to detail and process oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus points:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the cannabis industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salesforce and Tableau experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The base pay range for this position is $70,304 - $84,000 per year, and a competitive bonus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
